      {
        "start": 0.1,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "Let's design a program with objects and"
      },
      {
        "start": 2.5,
        "duration": 4.8,
        "text": "methods. We're working on the enrollment"
      },
      {
        "start": 5.1,
        "duration": 5.2,
        "text": "software for a school that students use"
      },
      {
        "start": 7.3,
        "duration": 5.9,
        "text": "to sign up for courses. Each available"
      },
      {
        "start": 10.3,
        "duration": 5.1,
        "text": "course has a title, an instructor, a"
      },
      {
        "start": 13.2,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "capacity, and a list of the students"
      },
      {
        "start": 15.4,
        "duration": 4.3,
        "text": "enrolled. The capacity tells us the"
      },
      {
        "start": 18.2,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "maximum number of students the course"
      },
      {
        "start": 19.8,
        "duration": 5.9,
        "text": "can hold. We want each course to keep"
      },
      {
        "start": 23.0,
        "duration": 6.5,
        "text": "track of its own information. So, we'll"
      },
      {
        "start": 25.7,
        "duration": 6.6,
        "text": "want a course type. In terms of methods,"
      },
      {
        "start": 29.5,
        "duration": 7.0,
        "text": "a course supports two key actions. A"
      },
      {
        "start": 32.2,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "student can enroll or unenroll."
      },
      {
        "start": 36.5,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "So, let's write out our class"
      },
      {
        "start": 38.0,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "definition. As always, we'll start with"
      },
      {
        "start": 40.5,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "our init method. So, we can set up the"
      },
      {
        "start": 42.6,
        "duration": 4.8,
        "text": "attributes for a course object. The"
      },
      {
        "start": 45.0,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "syntax always looks the same. We take"
      },
      {
        "start": 47.4,
        "duration": 5.4,
        "text": "our parameters and we store them on the"
      },
      {
        "start": 49.7,
        "duration": 6.2,
        "text": "object except our roster attribute,"
      },
      {
        "start": 52.9,
        "duration": 7.0,
        "text": "which we want to start out empty. So, we"
      },
      {
        "start": 55.8,
        "duration": 6.7,
        "text": "set it to an empty list."
      },
      {
        "start": 59.9,
        "duration": 5.3,
        "text": "Before we get too deep, let's test this."
      },
      {
        "start": 62.6,
        "duration": 7.5,
        "text": "We go back to main.py, import the course"
      },
      {
        "start": 65.2,
        "duration": 4.8,
        "text": "module, and then create a course object."
      },
      {
        "start": 70.5,
        "duration": 5.1,
        "text": "But when I print my course, we get this"
      },
      {
        "start": 72.9,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "not so useful representation."
      },
      {
        "start": 75.6,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "Instead, when I print a course, I want"
      },
      {
        "start": 77.9,
        "duration": 5.6,
        "text": "to actually show information about that"
      },
      {
        "start": 80.2,
        "duration": 6.0,
        "text": "course. So let's tell Python how to"
      },
      {
        "start": 83.5,
        "duration": 6.1,
        "text": "represent a course object as a string"
      },
      {
        "start": 86.2,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "using the special string method so"
      },
      {
        "start": 89.6,
        "duration": 7.8,
        "text": "Python can find it. We need to use the"
      },
      {
        "start": 92.0,
        "duration": 7.2,
        "text": "exact name underscore str"
      },
      {
        "start": 97.4,
        "duration": 5.4,
        "text": "and since it's a method it needs to take"
      },
      {
        "start": 99.2,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "the object as its first parameter."
      },
      {
        "start": 102.7,
        "duration": 4.6,
        "text": "What should a course look like? Well,"
      },
      {
        "start": 105.0,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "that's up to us as the programmer. Uh"
      },
